EXPERIMENTAL SITE.
SAPHIR REACTOR AT PSI, SWITZERLAND.
THE TARGETS WERE EXPOSED TO THE LARGE THERMAL
NEUTRON FLUX INSIDE A TANGENTIAL REACTOR CHANNEL.
.THERMAL NEUTRON SPECTRUM, WITH A FLUX OF 3.E+13
NEUTRONS/CM2/SEC.
.THREE TARGETS WERE USED, A 60 MG NATURAL IRIDIUM
SAMPLE, A 20 MG SAMPLE ENRICHED TO 88.8 PER CENT IN
IR-191, AND A 30 MG SAMPLE ENRICHED TO 98.7 PER CENT
IN IR-193. THE TARGETS WERE PLACED INSIDE THE TANGEN-
TIAL REACTOR CHANNEL.
IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY.
.THE INTENSITIES AND THE ENERGIES OF THE LOW-ENERGY
SECONDARY TRANSITIONS WERE DETERMINED WITH A HIGH-
RESOLUTION CURVED-CRYSTAL SPECTROMETER IN DU MOND
GEOMETRY. THE SPECTROMETER WAS EQUIPPED WITH A QUARTZ
CRYSTAL REFLECTING FROM THE 110 PLANES. THE REFLECTED
LINES HAD A RESOLUTION OF 5 ARCSECONDS, FWHM.

x4freetext: EXPERIMENTAL SITE.
SAPHIR REACTOR AT PSI, SWITZERLAND.
THE TARGETS WERE EXPOSED TO THE THERMAL NEUTRON
FLUX IN AN EXTERNAL NEUTRON BEAM.
.THERMAL NEUTRON SPECTRUM, WITH A FLUX OF 2.E+07
NEUTRONS/CM2/SEC.
.THREE TARGETS WERE USED, A 4 G NATURAL IRIDIUM
SAMPLE, A 37 MG SAMPLE ENRICHED TO 86 PER CENT IN
IR-191, AND A 20 MG SAMPLE ENRICHED TO 98.1 PER CENT
IN IR-193.
IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY.
THE HIGH-ENERGY PRIMARY GAMMA-RAYS WERE OB-
SERVED USING A PAIR SPECTROMETER. THE CENTRAL DETECTOR
WAS A 3 CM3 PLANAR GELI CRYSTAL WITH A RESOLUTION OF
5 KEV FWHM AT 6 MEV. FOR THE EXPERIMENTS WITH THE
ENRICHED TARGETS A 20 CM3 GELI DETECTOR, HAVING A
RESOLUTION OF 4.5 KEV FWHM AT 6 MEV, WAS USED.

x4freetext: BROOKHAVEN HIGH-FLUX BEAM REACTOR,
AND REACTOR IN KIEV.
REACTOR NEUTRONS, FILTERED BY SCANDIUM AND IRON
FILTERS.
.MONOENERGETIC NEUTRONS OF 2 AND 24 KEV WERE OBTAINED
AT BNL BY FILTERING WITH SCANDIUM AND IRON, RESPEC-
TIVELY. THE 2 KEV BEAM HAD A RESOLUTION OF 700 EV
FWHM.
.MONOENERGETIC NEUTRONS OF THE SAME ENERGIES WERE
OBTAINED IN KIEV BY FILTERING WITH SCANDIUM AND IRON-
ALUMINUM. THE 2 AND 24 KEV BEAMS HAD RESOLUTIONS OF
0.7 AND 2 KEV FWHM, RESPECTIVELY.
.THE TARGET AT BNL CONSISTED OF 18 G OF IRIDIUM METAL
POWDER, ENRICHED TO 98.2 PER CENT IN IR-191.
.THE METAL TARGET IN KIEV CONSISTED OF THREE IR-191
SAMPLES OF 5.65 G, 1.17 G AND 2.57 G, HAVING ENRICH-
MENTS IN IR-191 OF 78.3, 84.7 AND 88.8 PER CENT, RES-
PECTIVELY. TO OBTAIN ISOTOPIC ASSIGNMENTS, ALSO A
23.2 G TARGET, ENRICHED TO 97.6 PER CENT IN IR-193,
AND A 160 G NATURAL IRIDIUM TARGET, WERE USED.
IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY, FOLLOWING AVERAGE
RESONANCE CAPTURE.
.THE ENERGIES AND RELATIVE INTENSITIES OF THE PRIMARY
TRANSITIONS WERE DETERMINED WITH A THREE-CRYSTAL PAIR
SPECTROMETER AT BNL. IT HAD A TYPICAL RESOLUTION OF
6 KEV FWHM AT 5 MEV.
THE ENERGIES AND RELATIVE INTENSITIES OF THE
PRIMARY TRANSITIONS WERE DETERMINED IN KIEV
USING A PAIR SPECTROMETER, HAVING A CENTRAL 27 CM3
GELI DETECTOR, WHICH WAS PLACED BETWEEN TWO 20 CM
DIAMETER BY 10 CM LONG NAI-TL SCINTILLATORS. THE DE-
TECTOR HAD A RESOLUTION OF 8 KEV FWHM AT 7 MEV.
.TO REJECT BACKGROUND GAMMA-RAYS FROM THERMAL CAPTURE
IN THE BNL MEASUREMENTS, IT WAS REQUIRED THAT EACH
LEVEL SHOULD BE DEFINED BY GAMMA TRANSITIONS IN BOTH
THE 2 AND 24 KEV SPECTRA. THE AVERAGE ENERGY DIFFE-
RENCE WAS 20.7 +/- 1.2 KEV.
